node.text: When your entire day is spent out on the field, it helps to have a machine built with efficiency and reliability. The T6 Dynamic Command™ has been DLG tested as the most fuel efficient tractor in its class. When asked, Harald said, “with a 28 cubic meter trailer connected it consumes 10 -11 litres per hour.” This is of course a very good value, but nevertheless you don’t miss anything in performance.” #LetsGetItDone

node.text: The BRAUD 9090X grape harvester offers the best in terms of quality and productivity, facilitating the work in the vineyards with innovative solutions that improve every aspect of the harvest. Discover its main features and the reasons why it is the ideal solution for Francesco and many other growers. #LetsGetItDone

node.text: The FR650 is equipped with a 4WD rear axle to cope with challenging harvesting conditions. Robert says, “That is always very important for us, because we always have many hills in the terrain. Safe driving in all situations. And there are never any problems.” #LetsGetItDone

node.text: New Holland Ground Speed Management II, GSM II, is more than just an automated transmission shift system. With CVT-like functionality, it uses a combination of data relating to engine load, forward speed and operator setting, to manage both engine and transmission speeds to optimize performance and economy. Simple to set up and extremely efficient, GSM is well proven and dependable.

node.text: New Holland’s NutriSense system – awarded the Silver Medal at the SIMA Innovation Awards 2021 - provides farmers with valuable crop nutrient data from every area of their field. The farmer can visualise this agronomic data with an intuitive, user-friendly interface on their MyPLM™  Connect portal and use it to make informed decisions that will enable them to market their crops most profitably and/or to improve the animal feed ration content and quality in livestock farming.
